OL,3,CWill Rayner take the chance to seize
OL,4,CLabour leadership? She's not ruling it
OL,5,Cout
OL,7,FIt's not often that I sit down to
OL,8,Finterview a politician and have no
OL,9,Fidea what they are about to say.
OL,11,FWhen Angela Rayner arrived for her
OL,12,Ffirst TV interview since resigning as
OL,13,Fdeputy prime minister last year, there
OL,14,Fwas one question her advisers had not
OL,15,Fyet answered.
OL,17,FWas she about to make a bid for No 10?
OL,19,F"I would not trigger the prime
OL,20,Fminister" and start a leadership
OL,21,Fcontest, she told me.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31102
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1778767870
OL,3,CWill Rayner take the chance to seize
OL,4,CLabour leadership? She's not ruling it
OL,5,Cout
OL,7,FBut what if someone else triggered a
OL,8,Fcontest? Would she enter it?
OL,10,F"I'm not going to get into
OL,11,Fhypotheticals," she told me.
OL,13,FSo, not a 'no' then.
OL,15,F"Would you like to be prime minister?"
OL,17,F"I want to deliver as part of the
OL,18,Fteam," she told me.
OL,20,F"But would you want to lead the team?"
OL,21,FI asked her again.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1778767870
OL,3,CWill Rayner take the chance to seize
OL,4,CLabour leadership? She's not ruling it
OL,5,Cout
OL,7,F"We've got a leader", she replied.
OL,8,FAgain, not ruling herself out.
OL,10,FBut wait, what about all the
OL,11,Fspeculation that Angela Rayner had
OL,12,Fdone a deal with Andy Burnham and was
OL,13,Fgoing to support his bid for No 10
OL,14,Finstead of her own?
OL,16,FDid Angela Rayner and Andy Burnham
OL,17,Ftalk about a leadership pact when he
OL,18,Fcame round to her house recently?
OL,20,F"I'm not doing deals," she insisted.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1778767870
OL,3,CWill Rayner take the chance to seize
OL,4,CLabour leadership? She's not ruling it
OL,5,Cout
OL,7,FNo deal at all?
OL,9,F"No," she was very clear.
OL,11,FAgain, by not rolling in behind Andy
OL,12,FBurnham, she is keeping her options
OL,13,Fopen. Don't assume she'll make way for
OL,14,Fthe 'King of the North' - she might
OL,15,Fstill covet the crown herself.
OL,17,FEspecially as the reason for her
OL,18,Finterview was the conclusion of the
OL,19,FHMRC investigation (link to earlier
OL,20,Fpiece) into her tax affairs, which
OL,21,Fforced her resignation last year.
OL,26,@{D@Tpm|D@Fpn
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1778767870
OL,3,CWill Rayner take the chance to seize
OL,4,CLabour leadership? She's not ruling it
OL,5,Cout
OL,7,F"They've said that there wasn't any
OL,8,Fwrongdoing and that I didn't try to
OL,9,Favoid paying tax," she told me,
OL,10,Fdefinitively.
OL,12,FSo, cleared of any deliberate
OL,13,Fwrongdoing, has HMRC opened up her
OL,14,Fpath to No 10?
OL,16,FIf Angela Rayner does see herself as
OL,17,Fprime minister, she's not naive to the
OL,18,Fscrutiny it will attract.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31106
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1778767870
OL,3,CWill Rayner take the chance to seize
OL,4,CLabour leadership? She's not ruling it
OL,5,Cout
OL,7,F"It hurt me," she says of the HMRC
OL,8,Finvestigation into whether or not she
OL,9,Fpaid the correct stamp duty on her
OL,10,Fsecond home in Hove.
OL,12,F"The most distressing thing is that
OL,13,Fpeople felt that I was tax dodging or
OL,14,Ftrying to set up trusts to avoid tax
OL,15,For being careless... I had to then
OL,16,Ftalk about my son and his personal
OL,17,Fcircumstances, which isn't fair on
OL,18,Fhim. But I didn't want people to think
OL,19,Fthat the person they know me as
OL,20,Fsuddenly dropped all their values and
OL,21,Fwas just on the take."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31107
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1778767870
OL,3,CWill Rayner take the chance to seize
OL,4,CLabour leadership? She's not ruling it
OL,5,Cout
OL,7,FAll that criticism would only get even
OL,8,Fmore intense if she entered No 10.
OL,10,FBut if and when Wes Streeting sparks a
OL,11,Fleadership contest from the right of
OL,12,Fthe Labour Party, the soft left will
OL,13,Fwant to get behind their own candidate.
OL,15,F"I would not trigger the prime
OL,16,Fminister"
OL,18,FThat could be Angela Rayner or Andy
OL,19,FBurnham, or it could be Ed Miliband.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
